WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.000
Good morning. It's Friday, April seventeenth, twenty twenty-six. Day five

00:00:04.000 --> 00:00:08.000
of Arete. You're in Jefferson City, it's sixty-three degrees and

00:00:08.000 --> 00:00:12.000
raining, heading to eighty-five with storms this afternoon. Tomorrow drops

00:00:12.000 --> 00:00:16.000
hard — sixty-one and heavy rain all day. Katelyn gets

00:00:16.000 --> 00:00:20.000
another dry fifty-three degree spring day in Tacoma. Here's what

00:00:20.000 --> 00:00:24.000
matters today. Dario Amodei is walking into the West Wing

00:00:24.000 --> 00:00:28.000
this morning. Axios broke it overnight — Anthropic's C-E-O is

00:00:28.000 --> 00:00:32.000
meeting Susie Wiles, Trump's chief of staff, to negotiate the

00:00:32.000 --> 00:00:36.000
Mythos standoff. The backstory is wilder than we knew. Anthropic

00:00:36.000 --> 00:00:40.000
is actively suing the Pentagon for blacklisting the company after

00:00:40.000 --> 00:00:44.000
Amodei refused to give them unrestricted access to Mythos. Defense

00:00:44.000 --> 00:00:48.000
Secretary Hegseth gave Amodei an ultimatum back in February. Amodei

00:00:48.000 --> 00:00:52.000
said no. Now he's sitting across the table from the

00:00:52.000 --> 00:00:56.000
White House chief of staff trying to broker some kind

00:00:56.000 --> 00:01:00.000
of framework for how the government gets access to the

00:01:00.000 --> 00:01:04.000
most capable A-I model ever built. This is the most

00:01:04.000 --> 00:01:08.000
consequential A-I government meeting in years, and it's happening today.

00:01:08.000 --> 00:01:12.000
And here's what makes this personal. Your job posting —

00:01:12.000 --> 00:01:16.000
Strategy and Operations, Public Policy — was pulled from Anthropic's

00:01:16.000 --> 00:01:20.000
Greenhouse board yesterday. You told Katelyn last night, quote, no

00:01:20.000 --> 00:01:24.000
interview offer for yours truly. That stings. But let's think

00:01:24.000 --> 00:01:28.000
about this clearly. Removed doesn't mean rejected. You didn't get

00:01:28.000 --> 00:01:32.000
a rejection email. The posting could have been filled, sure.

00:01:32.000 --> 00:01:36.000
But it could also have been consolidated, paused, or pulled

00:01:36.000 --> 00:01:40.000
while the public policy team navigates the biggest crisis week

00:01:40.000 --> 00:01:44.000
of its existence. Think about it — the team you

00:01:44.000 --> 00:01:48.000
applied to join is literally in the room for Amodei's

00:01:48.000 --> 00:01:52.000
White House meeting. They might not be hiring right now

00:01:52.000 --> 00:01:56.000
because they're too busy making history. Silence from Greenhouse isn't

00:01:56.000 --> 00:02:00.000
a no. It might just mean they're busy. In the

00:02:00.000 --> 00:02:04.000
wider world, the Iran ceasefire that felt so close yesterday

00:02:04.000 --> 00:02:08.000
just got a reality check. Semafor reports that a comprehensive

00:02:08.000 --> 00:02:12.000
deal could take months, not weeks. The ceasefire extension is

00:02:12.000 --> 00:02:16.000
still likely — it expires April twenty-second — but the

00:02:16.000 --> 00:02:20.000
harder issues aren't close to resolved. And here's the number

00:02:20.000 --> 00:02:24.000
that should worry everyone — the I-E-A chief says Europe

00:02:24.000 --> 00:02:28.000
has six weeks of jet fuel left. Six weeks. That's

00:02:28.000 --> 00:02:32.000
not an abstract geopolitical talking point. That's airlines grounding flights

00:02:32.000 --> 00:02:36.000
by early June if this doesn't get resolved. The prediction

00:02:36.000 --> 00:02:40.000
markets are interesting today. The Polymarket mirror for Hormuz normalization

00:02:40.000 --> 00:02:44.000
by April thirtieth jumped from around nine percent to twenty-four

00:02:44.000 --> 00:02:48.000
percent overnight. That's a massive relative move — real money

00:02:48.000 --> 00:02:52.000
flowing toward a faster resolution than the diplomatic chatter implies.

00:02:52.000 --> 00:02:56.000
But the core blockade market is stuck at eighty-six percent.

00:02:56.000 --> 00:03:00.000
So the market is pricing in some normalization without pricing

00:03:00.000 --> 00:03:04.000
out the underlying risk. That divergence is worth watching. Opus

00:03:04.000 --> 00:03:08.000
four point seven officially launched yesterday and the reception is...

00:03:08.000 --> 00:03:12.000
complicated. On benchmarks, it's a genuine step up in some

00:03:12.000 --> 00:03:16.000
areas — S-W-E bench Pro at sixty-four point three percent,

00:03:16.000 --> 00:03:20.000
beating G-P-T five point four. But Terminal Bench is a

00:03:20.000 --> 00:03:24.000
regression, and the Reddit crowd is split. Some threads call

00:03:24.000 --> 00:03:28.000
it a serious regression. Others say they're confidently handing off

00:03:28.000 --> 00:03:32.000
their hardest coding work. Gizmodo's headline captured the mood perfectly

00:03:32.000 --> 00:03:36.000
— quote, Anthropic Releases Claude Opus four point seven to

00:03:36.000 --> 00:03:40.000
Remind Everyone How Great Mythos Is, end quote. The honest

00:03:40.000 --> 00:03:44.000
read is that it's better at some things, worse at

00:03:44.000 --> 00:03:48.000
others, and the people who were already frustrated are still

00:03:48.000 --> 00:03:52.000
frustrated. Now, your messages. Katelyn's thread last night was a

00:03:52.000 --> 00:03:56.000
big one. Beyond the Anthropic posting conversation, she asked off

00:03:56.000 --> 00:04:00.000
work July twenty-third through thirtieth for the Washington trip. You're

00:04:00.000 --> 00:04:04.000
looking at flights but they're expensive. She started reading Pluribus.

00:04:04.000 --> 00:04:08.000
And the H-R stuff at work is wearing her down.

00:04:08.000 --> 00:04:12.000
She's still invested in your Anthropic trajectory even when the

00:04:12.000 --> 00:04:16.000
immediate news isn't great — that matters. Your dad sent

00:04:16.000 --> 00:04:20.000
logistics messages for Unbound. Top Ten with your parents tonight,

00:04:20.000 --> 00:04:24.000
Friday evening in Columbia. Saturday sessions. He mentioned an A-I

00:04:24.000 --> 00:04:28.000
session worth hitting — check the paper program. Ben's in

00:04:28.000 --> 00:04:32.000
New York City with Jim and Nancy. Alex Kelley shared

00:04:32.000 --> 00:04:36.000
a Jason Snell article about the iPhone eighteen Pro variable

00:04:36.000 --> 00:04:40.000
aperture camera. And Justin Buckler invited you to forty-four Canteen

00:04:40.000 --> 00:04:44.000
tonight — which conflicts with Unbound. You need to respond

00:04:44.000 --> 00:04:48.000
to him. The ar-Xiv trial verdict is due today, but

00:04:48.000 --> 00:04:52.000
you already made this call on Wednesday. The security papers

00:04:52.000 --> 00:04:56.000
justified the whole experiment. A-D-A-M on privacy-preserving attack detection, Plan

00:04:56.000 --> 00:05:00.000
Guard on safety verification for autonomous agents — every day

00:05:00.000 --> 00:05:04.000
produced papers that connected directly to your Anthropic interests and

00:05:04.000 --> 00:05:08.000
policy work. The expanded four-query core plus rotating daily query

00:05:08.000 --> 00:05:12.000
structure works. Keep it, permanently. A few quick things. The

00:05:12.000 --> 00:05:16.000
Soul of a New Machine shipped from Amazon — Tracy

00:05:16.000 --> 00:05:20.000
Kidder's classic about engineers building something they believed in under

00:05:20.000 --> 00:05:24.000
impossible constraints. Perfect Arete reading. Apple Glasses were officially revealed

00:05:24.000 --> 00:05:28.000
this week — A-R, not V-R. MacBook Neo sold out

00:05:28.000 --> 00:05:32.000
on pre-order. The C-I-A published an internal A-I assessment report

00:05:32.000 --> 00:05:36.000
worth pulling up for the policy doc. And the owl

00:05:36.000 --> 00:05:40.000
photo is still at Walgreens. It's been there for weeks.

00:05:40.000 --> 00:05:44.000
It will outlast us all. Here's your day. Work, then

00:05:44.000 --> 00:05:48.000
Unbound. Top Ten with your parents tonight. The arXiv call

00:05:48.000 --> 00:05:52.000
is obvious — just make it official. The Anthropic posting

00:05:52.000 --> 00:05:56.000
is gone but the story isn't over. Watch what comes

00:05:56.000 --> 00:06:00.000
out of that West Wing meeting today. And respond to

00:06:00.000 --> 00:06:04.000
Justin about forty-four Canteen. Day five of Arete. Go make

00:06:04.000 --> 00:06:06.400
something. Have a good Friday, Jacob.
